title: jimmy fallon keith richards (18-09-2015) - First-Rls
description: Keith Richards is the celebrated guitarist of the Rolling Stones, who, alongside frontman Mick Jagger, has penned many of the band's greatest hits, including "(I Can't Get No) Satisfaction," "Ruby Tuesday," and "Sympathy For The Devil." Richards has played guitar on the Stones' over 60 albums and provided lead vocals on more than 25 singles. He has also released two solo albums, 1988's Talk is Cheap and 1992's Main Offender. Richards published his autobiography, Life, in 2010 and penned his first children's book, Gus & Me: The Story of My Granddad and My First Guitar, in 2014. His new documentary, target="_blank">Keith Richards: Under the Influence, premieres September 18 on Netflix
